<a id="top"> </a><h1>Tenure-track Position, Brown University</h1>
<p>
The Department of Philosophy seeks to make an Assistant Professor 
tenure-track appointment--AOS: Metaphysics, Philosophy of Language, or 
Philosophy of Science/AOC: Open, with a preference for Philosophy of 
Science. This position would begin Fall 2012. The position requires 
undergraduate and graduate teaching, advising of graduate or 
undergraduate students, and some share in administrative 
responsibilities. To be assured of consideration, applications should 
reach us by December 1, 2011. To apply, please send a CV, a writing 
sample, and three letters of recommendation. Preliminary interviews may 
be held with some candidates at the American Philosophical meeting in 
Washington (December 27-30); other interview arrangements may be made 
for candidates unable to attend that meeting. Brown University is an 
Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer, and we encourage 
applications from women and minorities. Send applications to:
